Diagnosis.
Small size (3.0 mm) (
Fig. 31A
). Antenna yellow, with postpedicel varying from yellow to dark brown (
Fig. 31C
). Scutum rounded, as broad as mesopleuron in lateral view, from yellow to brown, prescutellar disc and pal cal covered with dense gray pruinescence (visible without magnifying) (
Figs 31A, B
). Femora slender; legs predominantly yellow (
Figs 31A, D
). Wing hyaline; pterostigma inconspicuous; second section of M 
1
slightly longer than crossvein r-m (
Fig. 31E
).
